{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775858210997,"sessionID":"ses_2869a6fcdffesb4bjHj9DaiIpE","part":{"id":"prt_d7965c2db001IVGJzvSD4P1AG2","messageID":"msg_d7965b84e0010OsCWz0wMU8RfB","sessionID":"ses_2869a6fcdffesb4bjHj9DaiIpE","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_e06bc68813614975a35782c2","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-014/README.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-014/README.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-014 — Valkey 存储实现\n2: \n3: **Module:** pkg/store  \n4: **Language:** Go  \n5: **Size:** S\n6: \n7: ## Summary\n8: \n9: Implement Valkey storage backend for the pkg/store module.\n10: \n11: ## Status\n12: \n13: - [x] Scaffold directory structure\n14: - [ ] Implement Valkey storage backend\n15: - [ ] Add unit tests\n16: - [ ] Add integration tests\n17: \n18: ## Notes\n19: \n20: See `notes/` directory for implementation notes and decisions.\n21: \n22: ## Source Files\n23: \n24: See `src/` directory for source code changes.\n\n(End of file - total 24 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-014 — Valkey 存储实现\n\n**Module:** pkg/store  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** S\n\n## Summary\n\nImplement Valkey storage backend for the pkg/store module.\n\n## Status\n\n- [x] Scaffold directory structure\n- [ ] Implement Valkey storage backend\n- [ ] Add unit tests\n- [ ] Add integration tests\n\n## Notes\n\nSee `notes/` directory for implementation notes and decisions.","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-014/README.md","time":{"start":1775858210968,"end":1775858210996}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775858210999,"sessionID":"ses_2869a6fcdffesb4bjHj9DaiIpE","part":{"id":"prt_d7965c841001ZjSqu7a8W1jayh","messageID":"msg_d7965b84e0010OsCWz0wMU8RfB","sessionID":"ses_2869a6fcdffesb4bjHj9DaiIpE","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_321ee63f419b44539da22a96","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-014/status.json"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-014/status.json</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: {\n2:   \"ar\": \"AR-014\",\n3:   \"title\": \"Valkey 存储实现\",\n4:   \"module\": \"pkg/store\",\n5:   \"language\": \"Go\",\n6:   \"size\": \"S\",\n7:   \"status\": \"initialized\",\n8:   \"created\": \"2026-04-11\",\n9:   \"completed\": null\n10: }\n\n(End of file - total 10 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"{\n  \"ar\": \"AR-014\",\n  \"title\": \"Valkey 存储实现\",\n  \"module\": \"pkg/store\",\n  \"language\": \"Go\",\n  \"size\": \"S\",\n  \"status\": \"initialized\",\n  \"created\": \"2026-04-11\",\n  \"completed\": null\n}","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-014/status.json","time":{"start":1775858210972,"end":1775858210997}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775858211001,"sessionID":"ses_2869a6fcdffesb4bjHj9DaiIpE","part":{"id":"prt_d7965cdea001I78f3fOBFH9JUg","messageID":"msg_d7965b84e0010OsCWz0wMU8RfB","sessionID":"ses_2869a6fcdffesb4bjHj9DaiIpE","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_317e4b7f8ecf487aa6443859","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-014/proposal.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-014/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Proposal: Valkey Storage Implementation (AR-014)\n2: \n3: ## Summary\n4: \n5: Implement the Valkey backend for the session storage interface in `pkg/store`, providing persistent sandbox metadata storage with indexed queries for garbage collection based on expiry and last-activity timestamps.\n6: \n7: ---\n8: \n9: ## Purpose\n10: \n11: The Valkey storage implementation provides an alternative backend for session persistence in the agentcube project. It enables:\n12: \n13: 1. **Session persistence**: Store and retrieve sandbox information using Valkey key-value storage\n14: 2. **Garbage collection support**: Maintain sorted set indices for expiry and last-activity based cleanup\n15: 3. **Deployment flexibility**: Valkey offers Apache 2.0 licensing and enhanced performance characteristics\n16: 4. **Atomic operations**: Use Valkey `DoMulti` to ensure consistent index updates\n17: 5. **Cluster awareness**: Support for comma-separated addresses and cluster-specific options\n18: \n19: This implementation is the focus of AR-014 and builds upon the interface defined in AR-012, running in parallel with the Redis implementation from AR-013.\n20: \n21: ---\n22: \n23: ## Scope\n24: \n25: ### In Scope\n26: \n27: - `pkg/store/store_valkey.go` - Valkey implementation using `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go`\n28: - `sessionKey()` helper function for consistent key construction (shared with Redis)\n29: - `makeValkeyOptions()` for environment variable parsing and client configuration\n30: - All `Store` interface methods implemented with Valkey fluent API\n31: - `DoMulti` operations for atomic multi-command operations\n32: - `loadSandboxesBySessionIDs()` helper using MGET optimization\n33: - Unit tests with mocked Valkey client\n34: - Integration tests with real Valkey instance (Docker-based)\n35: \n36: ### Out of Scope\n37: \n38: - Redis implementation (covered in AR-013)\n39: - Alternative storage backends (etcd, Consul, etc.)\n40: - Valkey cluster sharding strategies beyond basic comma-separated addresses\n41: - Connection pooling tuning beyond default settings\n42: - Valkey-specific features beyond standard Redis-compatible commands\n43: \n44: ---\n45: \n46: ## Impact Analysis\n47: \n48: ### Dependencies\n49: \n50: | Package | Purpose |\n51: |---------|---------|\n52: | `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go` | Valkey client library |\n53: | `k8s.io/klog/v2` | Structured logging for client options |\n54: | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types` | `SandboxInfo` type definitions |\n55: | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/store` | Store interface (from AR-012) |\n56: \n57: ### Affected Components\n58: \n59: 1. **Sandbox Orchestrator**: Will use `Storage()` to persist sandbox metadata\n60: 2. **Garbage Collector**: Will use `ListExpiredSandboxes` and `ListInactiveSandboxes` for cleanup operations\n61: 3. **Session Manager**: Will use `UpdateSessionLastActivity` for activity tracking\n62: 4. **Configuration System**: Must provide `VALKEY_ADDR` and `VALKEY_PASSWORD` environment variables when `STORE_TYPE=valkey`\n63: \n64: ### Backward Compatibility\n65: \n66: - This is a new implementation of an existing interface\n67: - No breaking changes to the `Store` interface\n68: - Configuration via environment variables (no config file changes)\n69: - Transparent backend swapping via `STORE_TYPE` environment variable\n70: \n71: ### Risk Assessment\n72: \n73: | Risk | Likelihood | Impact | Mitigation |\n74: |------|------------|--------|------------|\n75: | Valkey connection failures | Medium | High | `Ping()` method for health checks; connection retry in client library |\n76: | ZSET index inconsistency | Low | High | Atomic `DoMulti` operations ensure all-or-nothing updates |\n77: | Password misconfiguration | Medium | High | Clear error messages; `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false` escape hatch |\n78: | Memory bloat from orphaned ZSET members | Low | Medium | List methods tolerate missing keys; periodic cleanup recommended |\n79: | Cluster slot conflicts in MGET | Low | Medium | Document in code comment; use `ForceSingleClient` option if needed |\n80: | Cache inconsistency | Low | Low | `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE=true` option for cache bypass |\n81: \n82: ---\n83: \n84: ## Alternatives Considered\n85: \n86: ### Alternative 1: Reuse Redis Implementation\n87: \n88: **Approach**: Use the same client library for both Redis and Valkey\n89: \n90: **Pros**:\n91: - Less code duplication\n92: - Simpler dependency management\n93: \n94: **Cons**:\n95: - Valkey-specific optimizations not possible\n96: - `valkey-go` library provides better cluster support\n97: - Misses Valkey's enhanced features\n98: \n99: **Decision**: Use dedicated `valkey-go` client library for better Valkey-specific support.\n100: \n101: ### Alternative 2: Hash-Based Storage\n102: \n103: **Approach**: Store session data as Valkey Hash instead of JSON string\n104: \n105: **Pros**:\n106: - Partial field updates without full serialization\n107: - More efficient for small field changes\n108: - Native Valkey/Redis type\n109: \n110: **Cons**:\n111: - Complex nested structures (`EntryPoints` array) awkward in hashes\n112: - JSON marshaling already required for `SandboxInfo` type\n113: - Less portable if switching to other backends\n114: \n115: **Decision**: Use JSON string storage for simplicity and consistency.\n116: \n117: ### Alternative 3: TTL-Only Expiration\n118: \n119: **Approach**: Rely solely on Valkey native TTL instead of maintaining `session:expiry` ZSET\n120: \n121: **Pros**:\n122: - Simpler implementation\n123: - Automatic expiration handled by Valkey\n124: - Reduced memory footprint\n125: \n126: **Cons**:\n127: - Cannot efficiently query \"sessions expiring before time X\"\n128: - Last-activity tracking still requires ZSET\n129: - Inconsistent semantics between expiry and activity indices\n130: \n131: **Decision**: Maintain explicit ZSET indices for efficient range queries required by garbage collection.\n132: \n133: ### Alternative 4: Lua Script for Atomicity\n134: \n135: **Approach**: Use Lua scripts for `StoreSandbox` and `DeleteSandboxBySessionID` instead of `DoMulti`\n136: \n137: **Pros**:\n138: - True atomic execution on Valkey server\n139: - Reduced network round trips\n140: \n141: **Cons**:\n142: - More complex code and debugging\n143: - Harder to test and maintain\n144: - `DoMulti` provides sufficient atomicity for this use case\n145: \n146: **Decision**: Use Valkey `DoMulti` for better code clarity and easier testing.\n147: \n148: ---\n149: \n150: ## Implementation Details\n151: \n152: ### Valkey Store Structure\n153: \n154: ```go\n155: type valkeyStore struct {\n156:     cli                  valkey.Client\n157:     sessionPrefix        string\n158:     expiryIndexKey       string\n159:     lastActivityIndexKey string\n160: }\n161: ```\n162: \n163: ### Key Patterns\n164: \n165: | Purpose | Key Pattern |\n166: |---------|-------------|\n167: | Session data | `session:{sessionId}` |\n168: | Expiry index | `session:expiry` |\n169: | Last activity index | `session:last_activity` |\n170: \n171: ### Connection Configuration\n172: \n173: ```go\n174: func makeValkeyOptions() (*valkey.ClientOption, error) {\n175:     valkeyAddr := os.Getenv(\"VALKEY_ADDR\")\n176:     if valkeyAddr == \"\" {\n177:         return nil, errors.New(\"VALKEY_ADDR is required\")\n178:     }\n179:     \n180:     valkeyPassword := os.Getenv(\"VALKEY_PASSWORD\")\n181:     passwordRequired := true\n182:     if v := os.Getenv(\"VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED\"); strings.EqualFold(v, \"false\") {\n183:         passwordRequired = false\n184:     }\n185:     \n186:     if passwordRequired && valkeyPassword == \"\" {\n187:         return nil, errors.New(\"VALKEY_PASSWORD is required (set VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false to disable)\")\n188:     }\n189:     \n190:     valkeyClientOptions := &valkey.ClientOption{\n191:         InitAddress: strings.Split(valkeyAddr, \",\"),\n192:         Password:    valkeyPassword,\n193:     }\n194:     \n195:     // Optional flags\n196:     if v := os.Getenv(\"VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE\"); v != \"\" {\n197:         if disable, err := strconv.ParseBool(v); err == nil && disable {\n198:             valkeyClientOptions.DisableCache = true\n199:         }\n200:     }\n201:     \n202:     if v := os.Getenv(\"VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE\"); v != \"\" {\n203:         if force, err := strconv.ParseBool(v); err == nil && force {\n204:             valkeyClientOptions.ForceSingleClient = true\n205:         }\n206:     }\n207:     \n208:     if valkeyClientOptions.DisableCache || valkeyClientOptions.ForceSingleClient {\n209:         klog.Infof(\"Valkey client options: DisableCache=%v, ForceSingleClient=%v\",\n210:             valkeyClientOptions.DisableCache, valkeyClientOptions.ForceSingleClient)\n211:     }\n212:     \n213:     return valkeyClientOptions, nil\n214: }\n215: ```\n216: \n217: ### Method Implementation Summary\n218: \n219: | Method | Valkey API | Notes |\n220: |--------|------------|-------|\n221: | `Ping` | `B().Ping()` → string | Expect `PONG` response |\n222: | `GetSandboxBySessionID` | `B().Get().Key(key)` → bytes | Use `IsValkeyNil` → `ErrNotFound` |\n223: | `StoreSandbox` | `DoMulti`: `SETNX`, `ZADD expiry`, `ZADD last_activity` | Validate non-nil and non-zero ExpiresAt |\n224: | `UpdateSandbox` | `B().Set().Key(key).Value(val).XX()` | Response must equal \"OK\" |\n225: | `DeleteSandboxBySessionID` | `DoMulti`: `DEL`, `ZREM expiry`, `ZREM last_activity` | Clean up all references |\n226: | `ListExpiredSandboxes` | `Zrangebyscore` with `Min(\"-inf\")`, `Max(before.Unix)`, `Limit(0, limit)` + MGET | Skip missing keys |\n227: | `ListInactiveSandboxes` | `Zrangebyscore` on `last_activity` + MGET | Skip missing keys |\n228: | `UpdateSessionLastActivity` | `Exists` key (must be 1), then `Zadd` | Return `ErrNotFound` if missing |\n229: | `Close` | `cli.Close()` | Close Valkey connection |\n230: \n231: ### Atomicity Guarantees\n232: \n233: - `StoreSandbox`: `DoMulti` ensures all-or-nothing for SETNX + ZADD + ZADD\n234: - `DeleteSandboxBySessionID`: `DoMulti` ensures all-or-nothing for DEL + ZREM + ZREM\n235: - `UpdateSandbox`: Single `SET XX` command is atomic\n236: \n237: ### Error Handling\n238: \n239: - `IsValkeyNil()` → `store.ErrNotFound`\n240: - Connection errors → wrapped with context\n241: - `DoMulti` errors → fail fast with descriptive message\n242: - Type conversion errors → explicit error message\n243: \n244: ### ZSET Score Semantics\n245: \n246: | Index | Score Source |\n247: |-------|--------------|\n248: | `session:expiry` | `float64(sandbox.ExpiresAt.Unix())` on store |\n249: | `session:last_activity` | `float64(time.Now().Unix())` on store; `float64(at.Unix())` on update |\n250: \n251: ### MGET Optimization\n252: \n253: The `loadSandboxesBySessionIDs()` helper function:\n254: - Builds all `session:{id}` keys from ZSET results\n255: - Uses single `Mget` command for batch retrieval\n256: - **Note**: Keys should be in same slot for cluster deployments (documented in code comment)\n257: - Skips entries where MGET returns empty string (orphaned ZSET members)\n258: \n259: ---\n260: \n261: ## Configuration Reference\n262: \n263: ### Environment Variables\n264: \n265: | Variable | Required | Default | Notes |\n266: |----------|----------|---------|-------|\n267: | `VALKEY_ADDR` | Yes | - | Comma-separated addresses (e.g., `host1:6379,host2:6379`) |\n268: | `VALKEY_PASSWORD` | Conditional | - | Required unless `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false` |\n269: | `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` | No | `true` | Case-insensitive boolean |\n270: | `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE` | No | `false` | Set to `\"true\"` to enable `DisableCache` |\n271: | `VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE` | No | `false` | Set to `\"true\"` to enable `ForceSingleClient` |\n272: | `STORE_TYPE` | No | `redis` | Must be `valkey` (case-insensitive) for this implementation |\n273: \n274: ---\n275: \n276: ## Testing Strategy\n277: \n278: ### Unit Tests\n279: \n280: 1. **TestValkeyStore_Ping_Success**: Mock `Ping` returns `PONG`\n281: 2. **TestValkeyStore_GetSandboxBySessionID_NotFound**: Mock `Get` returns nil\n282: 3. **TestValkeyStore_StoreSandbox_NilRejected**: Validate input validation\n283: 4. **TestValkeyStore_StoreSandbox_Success**: Verify `DoMulti` commands\n284: 5. **TestValkeyStore_UpdateSandbox_MissingKey**: Verify `SET XX` behavior\n285: 6. **TestValkeyStore_DeleteSandboxBySessionID_Success**: Verify cleanup\n286: 7. **TestValkeyStore_ListExpiredSandboxes_Empty**: Limit <= 0 returns nil\n287: 8. **TestValkeyStore_UpdateSessionLastActivity_NotFound**: Missing session\n288: 9. **TestValkeyStore_MGET_ToleratesMissingKeys**: Orphaned ZSET members skipped\n289: \n290: ### Integration Tests\n291: \n292: 1. **TestValkeyStore_Integration_FullLifecycle**: Full CRUD operations with real Valkey\n293: 2. **TestValkeyStore_Integration_ConcurrentAccess**: Concurrent store/update/delete\n294: 3. **TestValkeyStore_Integration_IndexConsistency**: Verify ZSET consistency after operations\n295: 4. **TestValkeyStore_Integration_PasswordAuth**: Test with password authentication\n296: 5. **TestValkeyStore_Integration_ClusterAddresses**: Test comma-separated address parsing\n297: \n298: ### Test Fixtures\n299: \n300: ```go\n301: func newTestValkeyStore() (*valkeyStore, func()) {\n302:     // Use testcontainers-go or dockertest for Valkey container\n303:     // Return cleanup function\n304: }\n305: ```\n306: \n307: ---\n308: \n309: ## Acceptance Criteria\n310: \n311: - [ ] `valkeyStore` struct implements all `Store` interface methods\n312: - [ ] Key patterns match spec: `session:`, `session:expiry`, `session:last_activity`\n313: - [ ] `DoMulti` operations used for `StoreSandbox` and `DeleteSandboxBySessionID`\n314: - [ ] `ErrNotFound` returned consistently for missing sessions (via `IsValkeyNil`)\n315: - [ ] Environment variable parsing matches spec table\n316: - [ ] `makeValkeyOptions()` validates required fields and optional flags\n317: - [ ] `loadSandboxesBySessionIDs()` uses MGET optimization\n318: - [ ] All unit tests pass with mocked client\n319: - [ ] Integration tests pass with real Valkey instance\n320: - [ ] Code coverage >= 80% for `store_valkey.go`\n321: - [ ] Documentation includes usage examples\n322: - [ ] MGET cluster slot consideration documented in code comment\n323: \n324: ---\n325: \n326: ## References\n327: \n328: - Interface Definition: `session-store/design.md`\n329: - Specification: `session-store/spec.md`\n330: - AR-012 Proposal: `changes/AR-012/proposal.md` (base interface work)\n331: - AR-013 Proposal: `changes/AR-013/proposal.md` (Redis implementation)\n332: - Valkey Client Docs: https://github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go\n\n(End of file - total 332 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Proposal: Valkey Storage Implementation (AR-014)\n\n## Summary\n\nImplement the Valkey backend for the session storage interface in `pkg/store`, providing persistent sandbox metadata storage with indexed queries for garbage collection based on expiry and last-activity timestamps.\n\n---\n\n## Purpose\n\nThe Valkey storage implementation provides an alternative backend for session persistence in the agentcube project. It enables:\n\n1. **Session persistence**: Store and retrieve sandbox information using Valkey key-value storage\n2. **Garbage collection support**: Maintain sorted set indices for expiry and last-activity based cleanup\n3. **Deployment flexibility**: Valkey offers Apache 2.0 licensing and enhanced performance characteristics\n4. **Atomic operations**: Use Valkey `DoMulti` to ensure consistent index updates\n5. **Cluster awareness**: Support for comma-separated addresses and cluster-specific options\n\nThis implementation is the focus of AR-014 and builds upon the interface defined in AR-012, running in parallel with the Redis implementation from AR-013.\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-014/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775858210974,"end":1775858210999}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775858211005,"sessionID":"ses_2869a6fcdffesb4bjHj9DaiIpE","part":{"id":"prt_d7965d380001Acetg9D6BoquOv","messageID":"msg_d7965b84e0010OsCWz0wMU8RfB","sessionID":"ses_2869a6fcdffesb4bjHj9DaiIpE","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_c1a10952ba4f48cfa43ca9de","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-014/tasks.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-014/tasks.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-014 — Valkey Storage Implementation Tasks\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: | Item | Value |\n6: |------|-------|\n7: | AR | AR-014 — Valkey Storage Implementation |\n8: | Module | `pkg/store` |\n9: | Language | Go |\n10: | Size | S |\n11: | Design Stage | ST-3 (Completed) |\n12: \n13: ---\n14: \n15: ## Atomic Tasks\n16: \n17: ### Phase 1: Valkey Store Structure\n18: \n19: - [ ] **TASK-001**: Create `pkg/store/store_valkey.go`\n20:   - Define `valkeyStore` struct with fields:\n21:     - `cli valkey.Client` (from `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go`)\n22:     - `sessionPrefix string`\n23:     - `expiryIndexKey string`\n24:     - `lastActivityIndexKey string`\n25: \n26: ### Phase 2: Connection Configuration\n27: \n28: - [ ] **TASK-010**: Implement `makeValkeyOptions()` function\n29:   - Read `VALKEY_ADDR` environment variable (required, comma-separated)\n30:   - Split by `,` → `InitAddress` slice\n31:   - Read `VALKEY_PASSWORD` environment variable\n32:   - Read `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` (default `\"true\"`, case-insensitive compare to `\"false\"`)\n33:   - Read `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE` (ParseBool, if true → `DisableCache=true`)\n34:   - Read `VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE` (ParseBool, if true → `ForceSingleClient=true`)\n35:   - Return `*valkey.ClientOption`\n36:   - Error if `VALKEY_ADDR` empty or password required but empty\n37: \n38: - [ ] **TASK-011**: Implement `NewValkeyStore()` constructor\n39:   - Takes `*valkey.ClientOption`\n40:   - Creates Valkey client via `valkey.NewClient()`\n41:   - Returns `&valkeyStore{cli: client, sessionPrefix: \"...\", expiryIndexKey: \"...\", lastActivityIndexKey: \"...\"}`\n42:   - Error on client creation failure\n43: \n44: ### Phase 3: Core Store Methods\n45: \n46: - [ ] **TASK-020**: Implement `valkeyStore.Ping()` method\n47:   - Execute `B().Ping()` command\n48:   - Expect string response `\"PONG\"`\n49:   - Return error if not PONG\n50: \n51: - [ ] **TASK-021**: Implement `valkeyStore.GetSandboxBySessionID()` method\n52:   - Construct key: `sessionPrefix + sessionID`\n53:   - Execute `B().Get().Key(key)`\n54:   - If `IsValkeyNil` → return `ErrNotFound`\n55:   - Unmarshal bytes to `*types.SandboxInfo`\n56:   - Return error on unmarshal failure\n57: \n58: - [ ] **TASK-022**: Implement `valkeyStore.StoreSandbox()` method\n59:   - Validate: sandbox not nil, `ExpiresAt` not zero\n60:   - Construct session key\n61:   - Marshal sandbox to JSON\n62:   - Use `DoMulti` for atomic operations:\n63:     - `SETNX` session key with JSON\n64:     - `ZADD expiryIndexKey` with score=`ExpiresAt.Unix()`, member=sessionID\n65:     - `ZADD lastActivityIndexKey` with score=`time.Now().Unix()`, member=sessionID\n66:   - Check all responses for errors\n67:   - Return error if SETNX fails (key already exists)\n68: \n69: - [ ] **TASK-023**: Implement `valkeyStore.UpdateSandbox()` method\n70:   - Construct session key\n71:   - Marshal sandbox to JSON\n72:   - Execute `B().Set().Key().Value().Xx()` (key must exist)\n73:   - If response != `\"OK\"` → return `ErrNotFound`\n74: \n75: - [ ] **TASK-024**: Implement `valkeyStore.DeleteSandboxBySessionID()` method\n76:   - Construct session key\n77:   - Use `DoMulti`:\n78:     - `DEL` session key\n79:     - `ZREM expiryIndexKey` member=sessionID\n80:     - `ZREM lastActivityIndexKey` member=sessionID\n81:   - Check all responses for errors\n82: \n83: - [ ] **TASK-025**: Implement `valkeyStore.ListExpiredSandboxes()` method\n84:   - If `limit <= 0` → return `nil, nil`\n85:   - Execute `Zrangebyscore` with `Min(\"-inf\")`, `Max(fmt.Sprintf(\"%d\", before.Unix()))`, `Limit(0, limit)`\n86:   - Get session IDs from result\n87:   - Call `loadSandboxesBySessionIDs()` helper\n88:   - Return `[]*types.SandboxInfo`\n89: \n90: - [ ] **TASK-026**: Implement `valkeyStore.ListInactiveSandboxes()` method\n91:   - Same as `ListExpiredSandboxes` but on `lastActivityIndexKey`\n92: \n93: - [ ] **TASK-027**: Implement `valkeyStore.UpdateSessionLastActivity()` method\n94:   - Validate: sessionID non-empty\n95:   - If `at` is zero time → use `time.Now()`\n96:   - Construct session key\n97:   - Execute `Exists` key → must return 1\n98:   - If 0 → return `ErrNotFound`\n99:   - Execute `Zadd` with timestamp score\n100:   - Return error on failure\n101: \n102: - [ ] **TASK-028**: Implement `valkeyStore.Close()` method\n103:   - Call `vs.cli.Close()`\n104:   - Return nil\n105: \n106: ### Phase 4: Helper Functions\n107: \n108: - [ ] **TASK-030**: Implement `loadSandboxesBySessionIDs()` helper\n109:   - Takes `[]string` session IDs\n110:   - Build all `session:{id}` keys\n111:   - Use single `Mget` command for batch retrieval\n112:   - Add code comment: \"Keys should be in same slot for cluster deployments\"\n113:   - Unmarshal JSON, skip empty strings (orphaned ZSET members)\n114:   - Log warnings via `klog.Warningf()` for orphaned/invalid entries\n115:   - Return `[]*types.SandboxInfo, error`\n116: \n117: ### Phase 5: Testing (TDD)\n118: \n119: #### Unit Tests - Configuration\n120: \n121: - [ ] **TEST-001**: Create `pkg/store/store_valkey_test.go`\n122:   - Test `makeValkeyOptions()` with all env vars set\n123: \n124: - [ ] **TEST-002**: Test `makeValkeyOptions()` with missing `VALKEY_ADDR`\n125:   - Given: `VALKEY_ADDR` not set\n126:   - When: `makeValkeyOptions()` called\n127:   - Then: returns error\n128: \n129: - [ ] **TEST-003**: Test `makeValkeyOptions()` with comma-separated addresses\n130:   - Given: `VALKEY_ADDR=\"addr1,addr2,addr3\"`\n131:   - When: `makeValkeyOptions()` called\n132:   - Then: `InitAddress = [\"addr1\", \"addr2\", \"addr3\"]`\n133: \n134: - [ ] **TEST-004**: Test `makeValkeyOptions()` with `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE=true`\n135:   - Given: `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE=\"true\"`\n136:   - When: `makeValkeyOptions()` called\n137:   - Then: `DisableCache=true`\n138: \n139: - [ ] **TEST-005**: Test `makeValkeyOptions()` with `VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE=true`\n140:   - Given: `VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE=\"true\"`\n141:   - When: `makeValkeyOptions()` called\n142:   - Then: `ForceSingleClient=true`\n143: \n144: - [ ] **TEST-006**: Test `makeValkeyOptions()` with password required but empty\n145:   - Given: `VALKEY_PASSWORD` empty, `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` unset\n146:   - When: `makeValkeyOptions()` called\n147:   - Then: returns error\n148: \n149: - [ ] **TEST-007**: Test `makeValkeyOptions()` with `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false`\n150:   - Given: `VALKEY_PASSWORD` empty, `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=\"false\"`\n151:   - When: `makeValkeyOptions()` called\n152:   - Then: returns options with empty password\n153: \n154: #### Unit Tests - Store Methods\n155: \n156: - [ ] **TEST-010**: Mock test `valkeyStore.Ping()` returns PONG\n157:   - Given: mocked Valkey client returning PONG\n158:   - When: `Ping()` called\n159:   - Then: returns nil error\n160: \n161: - [ ] **TEST-011**: Mock test `valkeyStore.GetSandboxBySessionID()` with missing key\n162:   - Given: `IsValkeyNil` true\n163:   - When: `GetSandboxBySessionID()` called\n164:   - Then: returns `ErrNotFound`\n165: \n166: - [ ] **TEST-012**: Mock test `valkeyStore.StoreSandbox()` with nil sandbox\n167:   - Given: `StoreSandbox(ctx, nil)`\n168:   - When: called\n169:   - Then: returns error\n170: \n171: - [ ] **TEST-013**: Mock test `valkeyStore.StoreSandbox()` with zero ExpiresAt\n172:   - Given: sandbox with `ExpiresAt.IsZero() = true`\n173:   - When: called\n174:   - Then: returns error\n175: \n176: - [ ] **TEST-014**: Mock test `valkeyStore.StoreSandbox()` DoMulti atomicity\n177:   - Given: valid sandbox\n178:   - When: `StoreSandbox()` called\n179:   - Then: SETNX, ZADD expiry, ZADD last_activity all called\n180: \n181: - [ ] **TEST-015**: Mock test `valkeyStore.UpdateSandbox()` XX semantics\n182:   - Given: SET XX returns not \"OK\"\n183:   - When: `UpdateSandbox()` called\n184:   - Then: returns `ErrNotFound`\n185: \n186: - [ ] **TEST-016**: Mock test `valkeyStore.DeleteSandboxBySessionID()` DoMulti\n187:   - Given: existing session\n188:   - When: `DeleteSandboxBySessionID()` called\n189:   - Then: DEL, ZREM expiry, ZREM last_activity all called\n190: \n191: - [ ] **TEST-017**: Mock test `valkeyStore.ListExpiredSandboxes()` with limit 0\n192:   - Given: `limit = 0`\n193:   - When: `ListExpiredSandboxes()` called\n194:   - Then: returns `nil, nil`\n195: \n196: - [ ] **TEST-018**: Mock test `valkeyStore.ListExpiredSandboxes()` tolerates orphaned keys\n197:   - Given: ZSET returns IDs but some MGET return empty\n198:   - When: `ListExpiredSandboxes()` called\n199:   - Then: skips missing keys, returns found ones\n200: \n201: - [ ] **TEST-019**: Mock test `valkeyStore.UpdateSessionLastActivity()` with missing session\n202:   - Given: Exists returns 0\n203:   - When: `UpdateSessionLastActivity()` called\n204:   - Then: returns `ErrNotFound`\n205: \n206: - [ ] **TEST-020**: Mock test `valkeyStore.UpdateSessionLastActivity()` with zero time\n207:   - Given: `at = time.Time{}`\n208:   - When: `UpdateSessionLastActivity()` called\n209:   - Then: uses `time.Now()` for ZADD score\n210: \n211: - [ ] **TEST-021**: Mock test `valkeyStore.UpdateSessionLastActivity()` with empty sessionID\n212:   - Given: `sessionID = \"\"`\n213:   - When: `UpdateSessionLastActivity()` called\n214:   - Then: returns error\n215: \n216: #### Integration Tests\n217: \n218: - [ ] **TEST-030**: Create `pkg/store/store_valkey_integration_test.go`\n219:   - Requires Docker Valkey or testcontainers\n220: \n221: - [ ] **TEST-031**: Integration test `valkeyStore.Ping()` with real Valkey\n222: \n223: - [ ] **TEST-032**: Integration test `valkeyStore.StoreSandbox()` → `GetSandboxBySessionID()`\n224:   - Store sandbox\n225:   - Retrieve by session ID\n226:   - Verify fields match\n227: \n228: - [ ] **TEST-033**: Integration test `valkeyStore.UpdateSandbox()` XX semantics\n229:   - Store sandbox\n230:   - Update sandbox\n231:   - Verify updated fields\n232:   - Try update non-existent → expect `ErrNotFound`\n233: \n234: - [ ] **TEST-034**: Integration test `valkeyStore.DeleteSandboxBySessionID()` cleanup\n235:   - Store sandbox\n236:   - Delete\n237:   - Verify GET returns `ErrNotFound`\n238:   - Verify ZSETs don't contain session ID\n239: \n240: - [ ] **TEST-035**: Integration test `valkeyStore.ListExpiredSandboxes()`\n241:   - Store multiple sandboxes with different expiry times\n242:   - Query with `before` time\n243:   - Verify correct sandboxes returned\n244: \n245: - [ ] **TEST-036**: Integration test `valkeyStore.ListInactiveSandboxes()`\n246:   - Store multiple sandboxes, update some with `UpdateSessionLastActivity`\n247:   - Query with `before` time\n248:   - Verify correct sandboxes returned\n249: \n250: - [ ] **TEST-037**: Integration test ZSET index consistency under concurrent operations\n251:   - Multiple goroutines Store/Delete concurrently\n252:   - Verify ZSET indices remain consistent\n253: \n254: - [ ] **TEST-038**: Integration test `valkeyStore.UpdateSessionLastActivity()` full flow\n255:   - Store sandbox\n256:   - Update last activity\n257:   - Verify ZSET score updated\n258: \n259: - [ ] **TEST-039**: Integration test with password authentication\n260:   - Start Valkey with password\n261:   - Configure `VALKEY_PASSWORD`\n262:   - Verify connection succeeds\n263: \n264: - [ ] **TEST-040**: Integration test with comma-separated addresses\n265:   - Configure `VALKEY_ADDR=\"addr1,addr2\"`\n266:   - Verify client connects to cluster\n267: \n268: ### Phase 6: Documentation\n269: \n270: - [ ] **DOC-001**: Add godoc comments to `valkeyStore` struct\n271:   - Document purpose and fields\n272: \n273: - [ ] **DOC-002**: Add godoc comments to `makeValkeyOptions()`\n274:   - Document all environment variables\n275:   - Document default values\n276:   - Document error conditions\n277: \n278: - [ ] **DOC-003**: Add godoc comments to `NewValkeyStore()`\n279:   - Document parameters and return values\n280: \n281: - [ ] **DOC-004**: Add godoc comments to all `valkeyStore` methods\n282:   - Document Valkey API patterns used\n283:   - Document DoMulti atomicity guarantees\n284:   - Document error conditions including `ErrNotFound`\n285: \n286: - [ ] **DOC-005**: Document key patterns in code comments\n287:   - `session:{id}` for JSON storage\n288:   - `session:expiry` ZSET for expiry index\n289:   - `session:last_activity` ZSET for activity index\n290: \n291: - [ ] **DOC-006**: Document ZSET score semantics\n292:   - Expiry score = `ExpiresAt.Unix()`\n293:   - Last activity score = `LastActivityAt.Unix()` or `time.Now().Unix()`\n294: \n295: - [ ] **DOC-007**: Add code comment to `loadSandboxesBySessionIDs()`\n296:   - Document MGET cluster slot consideration\n297:   - Note: \"Keys should be in same slot for cluster deployments\"\n298: \n299: - [ ] **DOC-008**: Document environment variables in code comments or README\n300:   - All `VALKEY_*` variables\n301:   - Default values and required status\n302:   - Case-insensitivity notes\n303: \n304: - [ ] **DOC-009**: Add example usage in doc.go or example test\n305:   - Initialize Valkey store via `NewValkeyStore()`\n306:   - Call `Ping()` to verify connectivity\n307:   - Call `StoreSandbox()` to persist sandbox\n308:   - Call `GetSandboxBySessionID()` to retrieve\n309: \n310: ---\n311: \n312: ## Acceptance Criteria\n313: \n314: - [ ] `valkeyStore` struct implements all `Store` interface methods\n315: - [ ] Key patterns match spec: `session:`, `session:expiry`, `session:last_activity`\n316: - [ ] `DoMulti` operations used for `StoreSandbox` and `DeleteSandboxBySessionID`\n317: - [ ] `ErrNotFound` returned consistently for missing sessions (via `IsValkeyNil`)\n318: - [ ] Environment variable parsing matches spec table\n319: - [ ] `makeValkeyOptions()` validates required fields and optional flags\n320: - [ ] `loadSandboxesBySessionIDs()` uses MGET optimization\n321: - [ ] MGET cluster slot consideration documented in code comment\n322: - [ ] All unit tests pass with mocked client\n323: - [ ] Integration tests pass with real Valkey instance\n324: - [ ] Code coverage >= 80% for `store_valkey.go`\n325: - [ ] Godoc documentation complete\n326: - [ ] `Storage()` singleton supports `STORE_TYPE=valkey` (case-insensitive)\n327: \n328: ---\n329: \n330: ## Dependencies\n331: \n332: | Dependency | Source | Usage |\n333: |------------|--------|-------|\n334: | `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go` | External | Valkey client library |\n335: | `k8s.io/klog/v2` | External | Structured logging |\n336: | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types` | Internal | `SandboxInfo` type |\n337: | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/workloadmanager/types` | Internal | SandboxInfo alias source |\n338: | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/store` | Internal | Store interface (AR-012) |\n339: \n340: ---\n341: \n342: ## Implementation Order\n343: \n344: ```\n345: TASK-001\n346:     ↓\n347: TASK-010 → TASK-011\n348:     ↓\n349: TASK-020 → TASK-021 → TASK-022 → ... → TASK-028\n350:     ↓\n351: TASK-030\n352:     ↓\n353: TEST-001 → ... → TEST-040\n354:     ↓\n355: DOC-001 → ... → DOC-009\n356: ```\n357: \n358: ---\n359: \n360: ## Related ARs\n361: \n362: | AR | Title | Relationship |\n363: |----|-------|--------------|\n364: | AR-012 | Session Storage Interface Definition | Base interface work |\n365: | AR-013 | Redis Storage Implementation | Parallel Redis backend |\n366: | AR-014 | Valkey Storage Implementation | This implementation |\n\n(End of file - total 366 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-014 — Valkey Storage Implementation Tasks\n\n## Overview\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-014 — Valkey Storage Implementation |\n| Module | `pkg/store` |\n| Language | Go |\n| Size | S |\n| Design Stage | ST-3 (Completed) |\n\n---\n\n## Atomic Tasks\n\n### Phase 1: Valkey Store Structure\n\n- [ ] **TASK-001**: Create `pkg/store/store_valkey.go`\n  - Define `valkeyStore` struct with fields:","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-014/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775858210976,"end":1775858211002}}}}
