{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775858281277,"sessionID":"ses_2869a6fcdffesb4bjHj9DaiIpE","part":{"id":"prt_d79660f0f001KAF42xidYXq5TZ","messageID":"msg_d796606d0001xm3bszTdRgWH8t","sessionID":"ses_2869a6fcdffesb4bjHj9DaiIpE","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_a7f86430cbba461fa2df1701","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# Proposal: PicoD Command Execution API (AR-015)\n\n## Summary\n\nImplement the command execution API for the PicoD module in `pkg/picod`, providing secure and controlled command execution capabilities for sandboxed environments.\n\n---\n\n## Purpose\n\nThe PicoD command execution API provides:\n\n1. **Secure Command Execution**: Execute commands within controlled sandbox environments\n2. **Resource Limits**: Enforce CPU, memory, and time limits on command execution\n3. **Output Capture**: Capture stdout, stderr, and exit codes\n4. **Streaming Support**: Optional streaming output for long-running commands\n5. **Cancellation**: Support for command cancellation via context\n\nThis implementation is the focus of AR-015 and builds upon the sandbox infrastructure established in previous ARs.\n\n---\n\n## Scope\n\n### In Scope\n\n- `pkg/picod/picod.go` - Core PicoD structure and initialization\n- `pkg/picod/executor.go` - Command execution logic\n- `pkg/picod/limits.go` - Resource limit configuration and enforcement\n- `pkg/picod/output.go` - Output capture and streaming\n- `pkg/picod/security.go` - Security validations and sandboxing\n- Unit tests with mocked executors\n- Integration tests with real command execution\n\n### Out of Scope\n\n- Container runtime integration (covered in separate ARs)\n- Network namespace manipulation\n- Filesystem isolation beyond chroot\n- User namespace management\n- Distributed command execution\n\n---\n\n## Impact Analysis\n\n### Dependencies\n\n| Package | Purpose |\n|---------|---------|\n| `context` | Command cancellation and timeouts |\n| `os/exec` | Command execution primitives |\n| `syscall` | Process management and signals |\n| `k8s.io/klog/v2` | Structured logging |\n| `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types` | SandboxInfo type definitions |\n\n### Affected Components\n\n1. **Sandbox Manager**: Will use PicoD for command execution within sandboxes\n2. **Workload Manager**: Will invoke PicoD APIs for job execution\n3. **Security Module**: Will configure security policies for command execution\n4. **Monitoring System**: Will collect metrics from command execution\n\n### Backward Compatibility\n\n- This is a new module with no existing API surface\n- No breaking changes to existing components\n- Configuration via environment variables and programmatic API\n\n### Risk Assessment\n\n| Risk | Likelihood | Impact | Mitigation |\n|------|------------|--------|------------|\n| Command injection | Low | High | Input validation, allowlist-based command selection |\n| Resource exhaustion | Medium | High | Enforce strict CPU/memory/time limits |\n| Privilege escalation | Low | Critical | Run as non-root, drop capabilities, use namespaces |\n| Output buffer overflow | Low | Medium | Stream large outputs, enforce size limits |\n| Zombie processes | Medium | Low | Proper process reaping, signal handling |\n\n---\n\n## Alternatives Considered\n\n### Alternative 1: Use Existing Library (e.g., go-execute)\n\n**Approach**: Leverage existing command execution libraries\n\n**Pros**:\n- Less code to maintain\n- Battle-tested implementations\n\n**Cons**:\n- May not meet specific security requirements\n- Additional dependency\n- Less control over resource limits\n\n**Decision**: Implement custom solution for full control over security and limits.\n\n### Alternative 2: Shell-based Execution\n\n**Approach**: Execute commands via `/bin/sh -c`\n\n**Pros**:\n- Simple implementation\n- Shell features available\n\n**Cons**:\n- Security risks (shell injection)\n- Harder to control resource limits\n- Additional attack surface\n\n**Decision**: Use direct execve-style execution for better security.\n\n---\n\n## Implementation Details\n\n### PicoD Structure\n\n```go\ntype PicoD struct {\n    sandboxID     string\n    workDir       string\n    limits        *ResourceLimits\n    securityOpts  *SecurityOptions\n    logger        klog.Logger\n}\n```\n\n### Resource Limits\n\n```go\ntype ResourceLimits struct {\n    Timeout       time.Duration\n    MaxCPU        float64\n    MaxMemory     int64\n    MaxOutputSize int64\n    MaxProcesses  int\n}\n```\n\n### Security Options\n\n```go\ntype SecurityOptions struct {\n    UID           int\n    GID           int\n    Capabilities  []string\n    ReadOnlyFS    bool\n    NoNetwork     bool\n}\n```\n\n### Command Execution API\n\n```go\ntype Command struct {\n    Path    string\n    Args    []string\n    Env     []string\n    Dir     string\n    Stdin   io.Reader\n    Stdout  io.Writer\n    Stderr  io.Writer\n}\n\ntype CommandResult struct {\n    ExitCode   int\n    Stdout     []byte\n    Stderr     []byte\n    Duration   time.Duration\n    OOMKilled  bool\n    Timeout    bool\n}\n\nfunc (p *PicoD) Run(ctx context.Context, cmd *Command) (*CommandResult, error)\nfunc (p *PicoD) Start(ctx context.Context, cmd *Command) (*Process, error)\nfunc (p *Process) Wait() (*CommandResult, error)\nfunc (p *Process) Kill(signal os.Signal) error\n```\n\n---\n\n## Configuration Reference\n\n### Environment Variables\n\n| Variable | Required | Default | Notes |\n|----------|----------|---------|-------|\n| `PICOD_WORKDIR` | No | `/tmp/picod` | Base working directory |\n| `PICOD_DEFAULT_TIMEOUT` | No | `30s` | Default command timeout |\n| `PICOD_MAX_MEMORY` | No | `128Mi` | Default memory limit |\n| `PICOD_MAX_CPU` | No | `1.0` | Default CPU limit |\n\n---\n\n## Testing Strategy\n\n### Unit Tests\n\n1. **TestPicoD_Run_Success**: Basic command execution\n2. **TestPicoD_Run_Timeout**: Command exceeds timeout\n3. **TestPicoD_Run_OOM**: Command exceeds memory limit\n4. **TestPicoD_Run_Cancelled**: Context cancellation\n5. **TestPicoD_OutputCapture**: Stdout/stderr capture\n6. **TestPicoD_SecurityValidation**: Invalid commands rejected\n\n### Integration Tests\n\n1. **TestPicoD_Integration_FullLifecycle**: Full execution flow\n2. **TestPicoD_Integration_Concurrent**: Multiple concurrent commands\n3. **TestPicoD_Integration_ResourceLimits**: Verify limits are enforced\n\n---\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] `PicoD` struct implements all required methods\n- [ ] Resource limits are enforced (timeout, CPU, memory)\n- [ ] Output capture works correctly\n- [ ] Cancellation via context is supported\n- [ ] Security validations prevent dangerous operations\n- [ ] All unit tests pass\n- [ ] Integration tests pass\n- [ ] Code coverage >= 80%\n- [ ] Documentation includes usage examples\n\n---\n\n## References\n\n- Sandbox Infrastructure: `changes/AR-012/proposal.md`\n- Session Storage: `changes/AR-013/proposal.md`\n- Valkey Storage: `changes/AR-014/proposal.md`\n","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-015/proposal.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-015/proposal.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-015/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775858281258,"end":1775858281275}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775858281279,"sessionID":"ses_2869a6fcdffesb4bjHj9DaiIpE","part":{"id":"prt_d796682c9001Wjo5RGiF5uL64y","messageID":"msg_d796606d0001xm3bszTdRgWH8t","sessionID":"ses_2869a6fcdffesb4bjHj9DaiIpE","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_3520dddce8814dfc8f61b4d7","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# AR-015 — PicoD 命令执行 API Tasks\n\n## Overview\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-015 — PicoD 命令执行 API |\n| Module | `pkg/picod` |\n| Language | Go |\n| Size | M |\n| Design Stage | ST-2 (In Progress) |\n\n---\n\n## Atomic Tasks\n\n### Phase 1: Core Structure\n\n- [ ] **TASK-001**: Create `pkg/picod/picod.go`\n  - Define `PicoD` struct with fields:\n    - `sandboxID string`\n    - `workDir string`\n    - `limits *ResourceLimits`\n    - `securityOpts *SecurityOptions`\n    - `logger klog.Logger`\n  - Implement `New(sandboxID string, opts ...Option) *PicoD` constructor\n\n### Phase 2: Resource Limits\n\n- [ ] **TASK-010**: Create `pkg/picod/limits.go`\n  - Define `ResourceLimits` struct\n  - Define `SecurityOptions` struct\n  - Implement option builder pattern:\n    - `WithTimeout(d time.Duration) Option`\n    - `WithMaxMemory(bytes int64) Option`\n    - `WithMaxCPU(cores float64) Option`\n    - `WithMaxOutputSize(bytes int64) Option`\n    - `WithMaxProcesses(count int) Option`\n    - `WithUID(uid int) Option`\n    - `WithGID(gid int) Option`\n    - `WithReadOnlyFS() Option`\n    - `WithNoNetwork() Option`\n\n### Phase 3: Command Execution\n\n- [ ] **TASK-020**: Create `pkg/picod/executor.go`\n  - Define `Command` struct\n  - Define `CommandResult` struct\n  - Define `Process` struct\n  - Implement `Run(ctx context.Context, cmd *Command) (*CommandResult, error)`\n  - Implement `Start(ctx context.Context, cmd *Command) (*Process, error)`\n  - Implement `Process.Wait() (*CommandResult, error)`\n  - Implement `Process.Kill(signal os.Signal) error`\n\n### Phase 4: Output Handling\n\n- [ ] **TASK-030**: Create `pkg/picod/output.go`\n  - Implement output capture with size limits\n  - Implement streaming output support\n  - Implement output buffer management\n\n### Phase 5: Security\n\n- [ ] **TASK-040**: Create `pkg/picod/security.go`\n  - Implement command validation\n  - Implement allowlist checking\n  - Implement path traversal prevention\n  - Implement capability dropping\n\n### Phase 6: Testing (TDD)\n\n#### Unit Tests\n\n- [ ] **TEST-001**: Create `pkg/picod/picod_test.go`\n  - Test `New()` with various options\n  - Test option builder functions\n\n- [ ] **TEST-010**: Test `Run()` success case\n- [ ] **TEST-011**: Test `Run()` timeout\n- [ ] **TEST-012**: Test `Run()` cancellation\n- [ ] **TEST-013**: Test `Run()` output capture\n- [ ] **TEST-014**: Test `Run()` exit code handling\n\n- [ ] **TEST-020**: Test `Start()` and `Wait()` lifecycle\n- [ ] **TEST-021**: Test `Process.Kill()`\n\n- [ ] **TEST-030**: Test output size limits\n- [ ] **TEST-031**: Test streaming output\n\n- [ ] **TEST-040**: Test security validations\n- [ ] **TEST-041**: Test allowlist enforcement\n- [ ] **TEST-042**: Test path traversal prevention\n\n#### Integration Tests\n\n- [ ] **TEST-050**: Create `pkg/picod/picod_integration_test.go`\n- [ ] **TEST-051**: Integration test full lifecycle\n- [ ] **TEST-052**: Integration test concurrent execution\n- [ ] **TEST-053**: Integration test resource limits enforcement\n\n### Phase 7: Documentation\n\n- [ ] **DOC-001**: Add godoc comments to all exported types\n- [ ] **DOC-002**: Add godoc comments to all exported functions\n- [ ] **DOC-003**: Add usage examples\n- [ ] **DOC-004**: Document security considerations\n\n---\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] `PicoD` struct implements all required methods\n- [ ] Resource limits are enforced (timeout, CPU, memory, output size)\n- [ ] Output capture and streaming work correctly\n- [ ] Cancellation via context is supported\n- [ ] Security validations prevent dangerous operations\n- [ ] All unit tests pass\n- [ ] Integration tests pass\n- [ ] Code coverage >= 80%\n- [ ] Godoc documentation complete\n\n---\n\n## Dependencies\n\n| Dependency | Source | Usage |\n|------------|--------|-------|\n| `context` | Standard | Command cancellation |\n| `os/exec` | Standard | Command execution |\n| `syscall` | Standard | Process management |\n| `k8s.io/klog/v2` | External | Logging |\n| `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types` | Internal | Type definitions |\n\n---\n\n## Implementation Order\n\n```\nTASK-001\n    ↓\nTASK-010\n    ↓\nTASK-020\n    ↓\nTASK-030\n    ↓\nTASK-040\n    ↓\nTEST-001 → TEST-053\n    ↓\nDOC-001 → DOC-004\n```\n\n---\n\n## Related ARs\n\n| AR | Title | Relationship |\n|----|-------|--------------|\n| AR-012 | Session Storage Interface | Base infrastructure |\n| AR-013 | Redis Storage Implementation | Storage backend |\n| AR-014 | Valkey Storage Implementation | Storage backend |\n| AR-015 | PicoD 命令执行 API | This implementation |\n","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-015/tasks.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-015/tasks.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-015/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775858281263,"end":1775858281278}}}}
